Package: dicepro
Title: Semi-Supervised Deconvolution of Bulk RNA-Seq Data with Hyperparameter Optimization
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Kalidou", "BA",
           role  = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "kalidou.ba@u-bordeaux.fr"),
    person("Boris P.", "Hejblum",
           role  = "aut",
           email = "boris.hejblum@u-bordeaux.fr"))
Description: Performs semi-supervised deconvolution of bulk RNA-seq data.
    Known cell-type proportions are estimated using supervised methods
    (CIBERSORTx, CIBERSORT, FARDEEP, DCQ, or BayesPrism), while unknown
    components are inferred using non-negative matrix factorization (NMF)
    with L-BFGS-B optimization. Hyperparameters are selected automatically
    using a Pareto-frontier-based approach with knee-point detection,
    allowing application when the reference signature matrix is incomplete.
